nite. \\\\n\\\\nIn JdbcUtilsTest, I might set up a dummy Driver to test error handling when calling getConnection. I’ll also need to create a nested public class for InitialContext that can return DataSource. Implementing this seems to be a solid approach.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Investigating database settings**\\\\n\\\\nI'm looking into the static clinit serializer, which seems tough to handle after loading. Maybe it should be a separate test process? But that's tricky since the class may have already been loaded by the driver, so I might just skip that part. Also, I need to check the EVENT_LISTENER URL property for the DatabaseTest. It looks like there's an H2 setting with DATABASE_EVENT_LISTENER='class' that I need to confirm, so I'll search that next!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_s1RIAPW4tvp239opdelHykwC|fc_051b73de3e9519f60169f855f319188193ad5d900ff80cab61\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"EVENT_LISTENER|JAVA_OBJECT_SERIALIZER|TABLE_ENGINE|AUTHENTICATOR|CREATE AGGREGATE|CREATE TRIGGER|ALIAS\\\" /home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/main/extracted -n | head -100\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 616, \"output\": 676, \"cacheRead\": 30208, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 31500, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777882595870, \"responseId\": \"resp_051b73de3e9519f60169f855e4c7108193b9411582f56a510d\"}}\n3231:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering test class organization**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the agent won't record the h2 package test helper class, which is interesting. It seems that including metadata for